{:claim-registry/version 1
 :claim-registry/description
  "Global claim definitions for all benchmark packs. Each entry declares
   the purpose, property types, related concepts, invariants, and evaluator
   reference for one claim keyword. The evaluator implementation lives in
   resolver-sim.benchmark.claims/evaluator-registry.

   EVALUATOR NAMING CONVENTION:
   Level 1 mechanical claims (evidence-root-present, replay-result-present,
   etc.) use the claim's keyword as the evaluator keyword directly — no
   :claim/ prefix. Level 2+ claims (with invariant-backed evaluators) use
   the full :claim/<id> keyword as the evaluator keyword. In both cases,
   the evaluator keyword is identical to the claim ID. This is a deliberate
   convention: evaluator ID = claim ID, not a separate namespace."

 :claims
 [{:claim/id :evidence-root-present
   :claim/title "Evidence root present"
   :claim/description "Each scenario produces an evidence root hash."
   :claim/property-types #{:integrity}
   :claim/concepts #{:verifiable-assurance/forensic-confidence}
   :claim/invariants []
   :claim/evaluator :evidence-root-present}

  {:claim/id :replay-result-present
   :claim/title "Replay result present"
